# Usage Instructions

**You can use Bitwarden with Firefox (Socks5 Proxy enabled) or Tor Browser.**

1. Open the browser and visit the add-ons section.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

3. Search for Bitwarden and click Add to Firefox.

Image for post

4. Access the Bitwarden settings.

Image for post

5. Copy your Bitwarden Tor onion URL from your Companion App and paste it into the Self Hosted Environment  Server URL field. Add http:// (NOT https://) to the frontend of the onion URL. Then click Save.

Image for post

6. Click Create Account and fill in the required fields.

This *does not* mean you are creating an account with Bitwarden or any other third party. You are creating an account with yourself on your own Embassy. Its awesome!

Image for post

## Keep in Mind

With great power comes great responsibility. This is a self-hosted password management solution, which means it comes with certain responsibilities. For instance, if you uninstall Bitwarden from your Embassy and have not made any backups, your passwords are gone forever. There is no means of recovering them. If your Embassy is offline or Bitwarden is not running, you will not be able to use your password manager until you reconnect to the Internet and/or restart Bitwarden.
